 =20
Brad Jacobs is a successful businessman =E2=80=9Cwho built multibillion-dol=
lar companies in logistics and other sectors through acquisitions.=E2=80=9D=
 Last year, he decided that he will next get into=C2=A0the business of roll=
ing up companies that distribute building products. To do this, he started =
a company called QXO Inc., made himself the chairman and=C2=A0chief executi=
ve officer, picked a team, and funded the company=C2=A0with=C2=A0$900 milli=
on of his own money and $100 million from outside investors.Jacobs has done=
 well in the past, and people want to back him, so QXO was a hot enough tic=
ket that last week =E2=80=94=C2=A0just a week after Jacobs put in his own m=
oney, and before he acquired any businesses=C2=A0=E2=80=94=C2=A0QXO was abl=
e to raise an additional $3.5 billion by selling stock and warrants private=
ly to=C2=A0=E2=80=9Ccertain institutional and accredited investors.=E2=80=
=9D (Bloomberg News reported that the investors include affiliates of=C2=A0=
the 3G Capital founders and the Walton family, as well as T. Rowe Price.) T=
