: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">writes</a>:=
 =E2=80=9COne story is, [Tesla=E2=80=99s institutional shareholders] agree =
that fiduciary litigation is rent-seeking, contrary to shareholder interest=
s, and does nothing more than distract boards from doing their actual jobs.=
  In this story, Tesla=E2=80=99s shareholders voted to limit the nuisances =
that threatened the ability of Elon Musk to run the company as he sees fit =
=E2=80=93 in a manner that would ultimately maximize the benefits to Tesla =
shareholders.  In other words, fiduciary litigation is too powerful, in tha=
t it inhibits too much managerial flexibility by imposing inappropriate one=
-size-fits-all standards.=E2=80=9D</p>
